&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;0 0 []&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Associate Brand Marketing Manager&lt;/strong&gt; is a key stakeholder in menu innovation and marketing strategy and execution, playing an integral role in shaping the future of sweetgreen. This position will be a key contributing member of the Brand Marketing team by supporting complex, cross-functional workstreams across our menu calendar, go-to-market campaigns, brand experiences, and product launches. This role will also manage cross-functional relationships and own brand and business performance analysis within the competitive landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Brand Manager will be a part of the Brand team. You&#39;ll be joining a team that manages the organizational menu and marketing calendar, with a guest-obsessed, culturally driven mindset. Join us for the opportunity to make your mark on the future of food.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Associate Brand Manager, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Strategy and Creative Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop assignment briefs and brand strategy across new launches and ongoing menu programs, translating consumer and competitive insights into clear creative direction for internal teams and agency partners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead go-to-market planning and 360 execution for new product launches, partnering with channel teams across CRM, Loyalty/Digital, Social, and Marketplace to drive integrated rollouts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Foster a high-functioning working relationship with the internal Creative team and agency partners, managing feedback loops and approvals to bring breakthrough campaigns to life on time and on brand&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Menu Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate closely with the Culinary, Supply Chain, Operations, and Finance teams on menu innovation and ongoing menu optimization initiatives, driving ideation, consumer positioning, and launch readiness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support annual marketing calendar management and lead performance reporting across launches&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own product financials for relevant menu programs, contributing a clear financial understanding of the business&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project and Process Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage cross-functional communications, project timelines, and workback schedules to ensure seamless execution across all programs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Track and manage budgets across owned programs, including spend, POs, and reconciliation in partnership with Accounting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bring a business owner mindset to every program, balancing creative ambition with financial and operational reality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired traits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong communication, attention to detail, and organizational skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exceptional interpersonal, communication, cross-collaboration, and team skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to solve problems both independently and as part of a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Curious and positively resilient&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven project management skills with experience owning timelines and cross-functional workstreams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledgeable in AI tools and how to leverage them to optimize workflows and drive efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adaptable to a fast-paced work environment with shifting priorities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in using consumer insights and data to drive decision-maki

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Sweetgreen:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sweetgreen is on a mission to build healthier communities by connecting people to real food. We passionately believe that real food should be convenient and accessible to everyone. Every day in each sweetgreen, our 6,000+ team members make food from scratch, using fresh ingredients and produce delivered that morning. And in our local communities, we’re committed to leaving people better than we found them. We’re in the business of feeding people, and we’re out to change what that means.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sweetgreen is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Community Engagement&lt;/strong&gt; to activate our brand and engage our communities, earning attention beyond the four walls of our restaurants. This role owns organic social, regional, and field marketing, and experiential — prime channels where sweetgreen earns its place in culture. You will lead a multi-disciplinary team and work cross-functionally to ensure that every activation, collaboration, and community moment is not only on-brand but connected to measurable business outcomes. You are equally at home in a creative brainstorm and a performance review, and you know how to build things that last.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core responsibilities for the position include, but are not limited to, the following:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and inspire a team spanning organic social, field marketing, and experiential, setting clear goals, priorities, and career growth paths for direct reports and the broader team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own sweetgreen&#39;s organic social strategy and community voice across all platforms — building an engaged following, fostering authentic conversation, and driving user-generated content and cultural relevance in a way that reflects our values and resonates with our guests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and oversee the regional and field marketing function, ensuring sweetgreen shows up meaningfully in local markets through community partnerships, neighborhood giveback initiatives, new market activations, and grassroots programming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead sweetgreen&#39;s experiential execution by creating IRL moments ranging from large-scale tentpole events to intimate community experiences that deepen brand love and generate earned media&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build robust measurement frameworks to connect community investment to brand health, traffic, trial, and retention, and regularly communicate ROI and learnings to senior leadership. Model continuous improvement, with an equal passion for culture and an obsession with data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Brand, Creative, Culinary, Growth Marketing, Partnerships, and Restaurant Operations to integrate community programming into broader campaigns, product launches, and seasonal moments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage agency and event production partners, maintaining high standards of quality and accountability within budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in office 4 days per week at the Sweetgreen Support Center in Los Angeles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–10+ years of experience in brand marketing, community, social, and/or integrated marketing roles at a consumer brand, with at least 3 years leading multi-disciplinary teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise across organic social and at least two of the other pillars this role owns: field/regional marketing, community partnership marketing, or experiential — with genuine curiosity and confidence across all of them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to connect community and brand programming to business outcomes — you understand how culture drives commerce, and you can articulate that clearly to stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of building and scaling communit

